name: Starloka Saba Bali
address: Jl. Permata Pering No.88, Gianyar, Kec. Blahbatuh, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80581, Indonesia
review 1:
Can't complain! Nice pool, friendly staff, decent rooms!

The rooms could do with some more details, such as a bedside table.. but honestly I think you get what you pay for.

They had scooter rentals available for 100,000 a day
review 2: What a cozy place to stay, very quite, clean and spacious room with affordable price. A bit far from the city but it’s worth it. Thank you for your great service.
review 3:
Honestly I  don’t understand the good comment on this post. I never write but comments usually, but it’s an exception. I had a really good time in Bali, the local are so nice and friendly! But in the hotel, I so lazy stuff, the organization it’s so bad !!! Escape !!!
- they have a bar with any coffee at 7am in morning ok it can happen.
- You ask to rent a bike, they just have 1 bike, you ask them if they know a place where you can rent a bike “ look on the google “ no help, it’s rude but ok
- The worst was when we ask for a laundry services, we give them our dirty clothes. They said tomorrow night it’s ready, the next it was not and if we wanted we have to pay an extra. Ok that find we gonna wait, but when the next our clothes were ready. They mixed the white, and a white tee-shirt lacoste come back dirty!
When we ask for an explaination, suddenly they don’t speak English anymore! They refuse to give us a refund.
That our only vacation in family, my brother don’t have many brand clothes, and I can accept that people are lazy or disorganize, no one is perfect. We all have bad day, bad week or bad life, but when you make a mistake, just fix it, it’s not fair. We give them our clothe to enjoy, and we pay for the service.

Honestly you can find the same hotel everywhere in Bali, but for the service, how you deal with you customers who pay for the service. I don’t want to see how you treat people in you life.
review 4: Great value! Mordern clean room with smart TV, Staff are friendly and helpful and a nice pool.
review 5:
We have great stay here... cozy rooms (family room) cool temperature, hot water and excellence service..

A little bit far from downtown but you get calm and cozy atmosphere here..

++ the poll is great
-- no breakfast option, but you can get it delivered by nearby restaurant..

Thank you
